It’s been over three months since I left Mumbai after living there for almost three years.
I went with a clear goal, to return to my hometown someday. And three months ago, I did. I got a job back home and moved, just like I always dreamed.
But something changed…
In all the chaos and excitement, I realized I had left a piece of me behind, in that city I once called “overhyped.”
Mumbai grew on me. Slowly, silently.
It gave me independence, courage, and belief. It showed me I could be alone but never lonely, that I could dream and make those dreams real.
Thank you, Mumbai, for everything.
I get it now, no city hugs you like you do.
